### Intent-Specific Audience Profile

**Who they are:** Nonbinary, genderqueer, agender, and gender-fluid individuals aged roughly 16–32, spanning all nail-art experience levels. Many are deeply community-connected and follow enby/queer nail content on TikTok and Pinterest. Some are masc-presenting and want designs that don't push them toward a femme aesthetic they don't identify with. Some are maximalists who want the full glitter-and-rhinestone NB fantasy. Others want something more editorial and considered. The common thread: they want to see themselves in the designs, not just the colours.

**What they want from this post:** Inspiration. Real, varied, beautiful design ideas that feel enby — not just a flag on a nail. They want enough variety to find something that fits *their* aesthetic, and enough editorial framing to understand why certain designs work. They also want to feel seen and celebrated, not merely informed.

**What satisfies them:** A post that treats the NB colour palette as genuinely beautiful and versatile — not just a pride obligation. Design ideas that range from short and bold to long and elaborate. Language that uses their community's terminology naturally. Images (and descriptions rich enough to function as images) that make them want to book an appointment or reach for their polish immediately.

**What frustrates them:** Designs that feel like basic Google image results. Content that only shows one interpretation (usually a literal four-stripe horizontal set). Posts that use generic pride-flag language without any understanding of what nonbinary actually means or what the enby community sounds like. Inspirational posts that don't inspire.

